entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.direction=The direction the laser cutter fires.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.firingLength=The amount of time, in seconds, the laser cutter should fire for.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.cutSize=The size of the hole cut by the Laser Cutter's Laser, in pixels. Minimum: 8
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.cooldown=The amount of time, in seconds, the laser cutter takes to reactivate. If the cooldown is less than the amount of time to fire and reset the laser, the laser will activate as soon as possible.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.flag=(Optional) Session Flag that turns on the Laser Cutter.\nIf flag is left blank, no flag will be required to turn the Laser Cutter on.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.invert=If checked, the Laser Cutter will be off when the flag is set to true, and on when the flag is set to false.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.mode=Determines how the Laser Cutter fires.\nBreakbeam: Laser Cutter fires when walks into the line of sight of the Laser Cutter.\nIn Front: Laser Cutter fires when walks in front of of the Laser Cutter, ignoring solid blocks and terrain that may be blocking the way. The laser fired will still be blockable via terrain and solid blocks, however.\nPulse: The laser will attempt to fire as soon as the cooldown timer specified by 'cooldown' has expired.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.breakbeamThickness=Width of the breakbeam in Breakbeam / In Front mode. Not used if Laser Cutter is set to Pulse mode.
entities.LylyraHelper/LaserCutter.attributes.description.sliceableEntityTypes=(Optional) The full name of the type(s) of entity(s) the Laser Cutter can slice.\nUse commas to specify multiple Entity Types (ex:Celeste.Player,Celeste.FallingBlock,Celeste.CrushBlock).\nLeave blank to allow slicing of all types in your SlicerController.\nIf FrostHelper is installed, you can use either Full Names or Entity IDs (the text at the top of a window when you edit an entity, ex: fallingBlock, LylyraHelper/DashPaper).


#Dash Paper


entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.placements.name.DashPaper=Dash Paper
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.placements.description.DashPaper=A rectangular area that maintains a player's dash count when they dash inside it.\n\nDETAILS\n\nDash Paper is designed to be used with LylyraHelper's Slicers.\nDash Paper interacts dynamically with Slicers, meaning instead of spawning smaller Dash Papers upon being sliced,\nthe area that was sliced is directly removed from the Dash Paper, allowing for partial slices if the slicer is interrupted or when using instant slicing mode.\n\nNote that Dash Paper is the same as any Sliceable Entity and must be added to your SlicerController's Settings to be Sliced.\nSee the LylyraHelper Gamebanana page for more details on Slicers.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.placements.name.DashPaperScissors=Dash Paper (With Scissors)
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.placements.description.DashPaperScissors=A rectangular area that maintains a player's dash count when they dash inside it.\n\nDETAILS\n\nDash Paper is designed to be used with LylyraHelper's Slicers.\nDash Paper interacts dynamically with Slicers, meaning instead of spawning smaller Dash Papers upon being sliced,\nthe area that was sliced is directly removed from the Dash Paper, allowing for partial slices if the slicer is interrupted or when using instant slicing mode.\n\nAddtionally, Whenever the player dashes, Scissors are spawned on a side opposite the dash (ex:an Up facing dash will spawn scissors at the bottom of the Dash Paper).\nThese Scissors are equipped with Slicers and will Slice any entity in your SlicerController's Settings.\nScissors additionally kill the player upon colliding.\n\nNote that Dash Paper is the same as any Sliceable Entity and must be added to your SlicerController's Settings to be Sliced.\nSee the LylyraHelper Gamebanana page for more details on Slicers.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.spawnScissors=If checked, spawn Scissors when dashing on the Paper.\nScissors spawn behind the player at the edge of the Paper and move in the cardinal direction(s) dashed.\nDiagonal dashes spawn two scissors on both of the cardinals dashed.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.noParticleEffects=If checked, this entity does not emit particle effects (besides player trail effects)
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.noTrail=If checked, this entity will not add a trail of particle effects to the player when the player is inside the paper.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.sliceableEntityTypes=(Optional) The full name of the type(s) of entity(s) Scissors created by this Dash Paper can slice.\nUse commas to specify multiple Entity Types (ex:Celeste.Player,Celeste.FallingBlock,Celeste.CrushBlock).\nLeave blank to allow slicing of all types in your SlicerController.\nIf FrostHelper is installed, you can use either Full Names or Entity IDs (the text at the top of a window when you edit an entity, ex: fallingBlock, LylyraHelper/DashPaper).
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.regenerationDelay=How long in seconds before the paper should reset. Set to 0 to not regenerate / reset.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.decalStampData=(Optional) Data for decals to be rendered on the paper.\n\nTo use this feature, overlay any Foreground Decals you wish to stamp onto the DashPaper and press the "Set from FG Decals" Button.\nYou may remove the decals from the paper or scene after they have been added, as the stamp data will persist.\nThe decals will still need to be present in your /Graphics folder or the /Graphics folder of one your dependencies.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.wallpaperMode=What preset decals to add to your paper.
entities.LylyraHelper/DashPaper.attributes.description.wallpaperColor=Color of the paper.

#Deathnote

#Slicer Controller

entities.LylyraHelper/SlicerController.placements.name.SlicerController=Slicer Controller
entities.LylyraHelper/SlicerController.placements.description.SlicerController=Allows you to modify your Slicer Settings, for use with Slicers and Slicer entities such as Laser Cutters and Knife Spikes.\nSlicers cut entities into pieces when they are hit by a Slicer if that entity is specified in the Slicer Controller settings.\nSee the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for more details on Slicers.\nSlicer Settings are Session variables, meaning these settings will persist across room changes and save + quit, similar to Session Flags.
entities.LylyraHelper/SlicerController.attributes.description.sliceableEntityTypes=The full name of the type(s) of entity(s) you want to be Sliceable.\nUse commas to specify multiple Entity Types (ex:Celeste.Player,Celeste.FallingBlock,Celeste.CrushBlock).\nIf FrostHelper is installed, you can use names in Entity ID format (the text at the top of a window when you edit an entity, ex: fallingBlock, LylyraHelper/DashPaper).\nAdditionally, if FrostHelper is installed, you can use the "Set from Intersect" button to automatically set this field to the names of all Entities overlapping the Slicer Controller.\nNote that your finished map will require FrostHelper to function.

#Dependency Trigger

triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.name.main=Dependency Trigger
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.description.main=Sets a Session flag if a dependency is loaded.\nUseful if you want to make a map that has optional or even secret dependencies.\nFor instance, a map where you want to warn the player if another mod can interfere with the intended experience such as a visual mod.\nAlternatively, become Psycho Mantis and use this to make dialog or cutscenes only if another mod is currently active.
triggers.LylyraHelper/DependencyTrigger.attributes.description.dependency=The name of the mod to check for. ex: LylyraHelper
triggers.LylyraHelper/DependencyTrigger.attributes.description.flag=The flag to set if the dependency is found.
triggers.LylyraHelper/DependencyTrigger.attributes.description.invert=If checked, sets the flag value to false instead of true.

#Add Slicer Trigger

triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.name.Up=Add Slicer Trigger (Up)
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.description.Up=Adds an upward facing Slicer to Entities of a type or type specified.\nThe entity doesnt have to be slicable for the Slicer to be added\nThis slicer will slice entities specified by your SlicerController settings.\n\nExample: Add an upward slicer to the Player to let them break blocks above them like Mario.\nSee the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for more details on Slicers.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.name.Right=Add Slicer Trigger (Right)
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.description.Right=Adds an upward facing Slicer to Entities of a type or type specified.\nThe entity doesnt have to be slicable for the Slicer to be added\nThis slicer will slice entities specified by your SlicerController settings.\n\nExample: Add an upward slicer to the Player to let them break blocks above them like Mario.\nSee the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for more details on Slicers.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.name.Down=Add Slicer Trigger (Down)
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.description.Down=Adds an upward facing Slicer to Entities of a type or type specified.\nThe entity doesnt have to be slicable for the Slicer to be added\nThis slicer will slice entities specified by your SlicerController settings.\n\nExample: Add an upward slicer to the Player to let them break blocks above them like Mario.\nSee the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for more details on Slicers.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.name.Left=Add Slicer Trigger (Left)
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.description.Left=Adds an upward facing Slicer to Entities of a type or type specified.\nThe entity doesnt have to be slicable for the Slicer to be added\nThis slicer will slice entities specified by your SlicerController settings.\n\nExample: Add an upward slicer to the Player to let them break blocks above them like Mario.\nSee the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for more details on Slicers.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.name.All=Add Slicer Trigger (All)
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.placements.description.All=Adds an upward facing Slicer to Entities of a type or type specified.\nThe entity doesnt have to be slicable for the Slicer to be added\nThis slicer will slice entities specified by your SlicerController settings.\n\nExample: Add an upward slicer to the Player to let them break blocks above them like Mario.\nSee the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for more details on Slicers.\n\nNOTE: THIS VERSION IS NO DIFFERENT FROM ADDING ONE OF EACH SLICER DIRECTION (UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT), AND IS JUST FOR QOL. FOUR TOTAL SLICERS WILL BE ADDED.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.cutSize=The size of the hole cut by the Slicer, in pixels. Minimum: 8
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.direction=The side the Slicers added cut from. "All" will add four slicers to the trigger, one each of Up, Down, Left, and Right.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.entityTypes=The full name of the type of entity(s) to attach Slicers fto.\nUse commas to specify multiple Entity Types (ex:Celeste.Player,Celeste.SolidTiles,Celeste.CrushBlock).\nIf list is empty, Slicers will be added to all Entities in range of the Trigger.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.slicerLength=The maximum distance, in pixels, the Slicer extends beyond the attached entity's hitbox. Minimum: 1
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.roomwide=If checked, the trigger will attempt to add Slicers to all applicable Entities in the room, regardless of if they are inside the trigger.\nIf unchecked, the trigger will only add Slicers to Entities inside the trigger.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.singleUse=If checked, the trigger will only attempt to add a Slicer to the first applicable Entity.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.sliceOnImpact=If checked, the Slicer added will attempt to cut on the frame that it his a Cuttable Entity.\nIf unchecked, the Slicer will not attempt to cut until the Slicer no longer collides with the Cuttable Entity's hitbox.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.onLoadOnly=If checked, the Trigger will remove itself after the room is loaded.\nIf unchecked, the Trigger will be persistent and add Slicers to Entities spawned after loading as well, such as those created by the result of a Slicer cutting a Solid in pieces.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.flag=The session flag that needs to be active for the trigger to activate. Flag check is skipped if left blank.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.invert=If checked, the trigger will be off when the flag is set to true, and on when the flag is set to false.
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.sliceableEntityTypes=(Optional) The full name of the type(s) of entity(s) the Slicer(s) added can slice.\nUse commas to specify multiple Entity Types (ex:Celeste.Player,Celeste.FallingBlock,Celeste.CrushBlock).\nLeave blank to allow slicing of all types in your SlicerController.\nIf FrostHelper is installed, you can use either Full Names or Entity IDs (the text at the top of a window when you edit an entity, ex: fallingBlock, LylyraHelper/DashPaper).
triggers.LylyraHelper/AddSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.matchCutSizeToLength=Default the cut size to the length of the entity it is attached to.\nUses entity's width if up/down and height if right/left.

#Remove Slicer Trigger

triggers.LylyraHelper/RemoveSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.roomwide=If checked, the trigger will attempt to remove Slicers from all applicable Entities in the room, regardless of if they are inside the trigger.\nIf unchecked, the trigger will only remove Slicers from Entities inside the trigger.
triggers.LylyraHelper/RemoveSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.singleUse=If checked, the trigger will only attempt to remove a Slicer from the first applicable Entity.
triggers.LylyraHelper/RemoveSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.onLoadOnly=If checked, the Trigger will remove itself after the room is loaded.\nIf unchecked, the Trigger will be persistent and remove Slicers from Entities who are in range of the trigger after room load.
triggers.LylyraHelper/RemoveSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.flag=The session flag that needs to be active for the trigger to activate. If left blank, the Slicer will always be ready to slice.
triggers.LylyraHelper/RemoveSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.invert=If checked, the trigger will be off when the Session Flag is set to true, and on when the Session Flag is set to false.
triggers.LylyraHelper/RemoveSlicerTrigger.attributes.description.entityTypes=The full name of the type of entity(s) to remove Slicers from.\nUse commas to specify multiple Entity Types (ex:Celeste.Player,Celeste.SolidTiles,Celeste.CrushBlock).\nIf list is empty, Slicers will be removed from all Entities in range of the Trigger.

