entities.LylyraHelper/BigCloud.placements.name.main=Big Cloud
entities.LylyraHelper/BigCloud.placements.description.main=A Cloud, but bigger.
entities.LylyraHelper/BigCloud.placements.name.mainfragile=Big Cloud (Fragile)
entities.LylyraHelper/BigCloud.placements.description.mainfragile=A fragile Cloud, but bigger.
entities.LylyraHelper/BigCloud.description.fragile=If the cloud should temporarily despawn after being used.

#Shockwave Emitter

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.placements.name.ShockwaveEmitter=Shockwave Emitter
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.placements.description.ShockwaveEmitter=A machine that emits elliptically shaped shockwaves.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.focalRatio=Focal Ratio of the Ellipse.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.initialSize=The initial size of the shockwave in pixels.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.timers=Times to send out shockwaves after being turned on.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.shockwaveThickness=Size in pixels of the shockwave.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.expand=Rate of expansion of the shockwave in pixels per frame.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.breakoutSpeeds=How fast a player needs to be moving before they can "break out" of a shockwave (that is, move from the inside to the outside of the wave without dying), in units speed.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.flag=Session flag to turn the emitter on or off. Leave blank to keep always on.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.cycle=Whether or not the the emitter should stop after the last wave is reached or if it should cycle.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.absoluteMaxGlobs=Render optimization option. Controls the detail level on the back of the shockwaves.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.renderPointsOnMesh=Render optimization option. Controls the quality of the render mesh used for the shockwave.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.ignorePlayerSpeedChecks=Shockwaves track potential maximum speed the player can have to detect teleports and other modded entities. On slow moving /non-nyoom maps, this same code can lead to clipping through the shockwaves. Check if you don't use teleportation or fast movement of any sort.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.launchPower=(Knockback Mode Only) Multiplier to the knockback speed applied by shockwave.\nCan be specified as a comma seperated list to control it on a per shockwave basis.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.mode=What to do when the player is hit by a shockwave.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.renderMode=Energy wave: Will look like the shockwaves originally seen in Secret Santa 2024's map "???" (aka "Project Lightspeed") by Hydro0.\nDisplacement: Looks like the big eyeball's shockwaves at the end of Ch. 5
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/ShockwaveEmitter.attributes.description.noSprite=Removes generator sprite if checked.

#Auto Return Falling Block

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.name.AutoReturnFallingBlockUp=Auto Return Falling Block (Up)
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.description.AutoReturnFallingBlockUp=A falling block that falls up (against standard gravity).\nAfter coming to a stop, this block will return to its starting location after a short (specifiable) delay.\n\nThis entity is a port of the Auto Return Falling Blocks seen in "Spacial Rift" by TheDavSmasher in Secret Santa 3.\n\nThese blocks are Sliceable. (See "Slicer Controller" or the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for details).

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.name.AutoReturnFallingBlockDown=Auto Return Falling Block (Down)
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.description.AutoReturnFallingBlockDown=A falling block that falls down (with standard gravity).\nAfter coming to a stop, this block will return to its starting location after a short (specifiable) delay.\n\nThis entity is a port of the Auto Return Falling Blocks seen in "Spacial Rift" by TheDavSmasher in Secret Santa 3.\n\nThese blocks are Sliceable. (See "Slicer Controller" or the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for details).

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.name.AutoReturnFallingBlockRight=Auto Return Falling Block (Right)
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.description.AutoReturnFallingBlockRight=A falling block that falls right (sideways).\nAfter coming to a stop, this block will return to its starting location after a short (specifiable) delay.\n\nThis entity is a port of the Auto Return Falling Blocks seen in "Spacial Rift" by TheDavSmasher in Secret Santa 3.\n\nThese blocks are Sliceable. (See "Slicer Controller" or the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for details).

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.name.AutoReturnFallingBlockLeft=Auto Return Falling Block (Left)
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.placements.description.AutoReturnFallingBlockLeft=A falling block that falls left (sideways).\nAfter coming to a stop, this block will return to its starting location after a short (specifiable) delay.\n\nThis entity is a port of the Auto Return Falling Blocks seen in "Spacial Rift" by TheDavSmasher in Secret Santa 3.\n\nThese blocks are Sliceable. (See "Slicer Controller" or the LylyraHelper GameBanana page for details).

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.tiletype=What tileset to use with this block.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.climbFall=If the block should trigger on climb jump.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.behind=If the block should render behind or above other entities.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.resetDelay=A timer in seconds that must complete before the block can reactivate, starting after the block returns to its starting location.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.flagOnReset=(Optional) The flag to set when the falling block returns to its original location
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.flagOnFall=(Optional) The flag to set when the falling block starts falling.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.flagOnLand=(Optional) The flag to set when the falling block lands.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.flagTrigger=The flag that needs to be active for this falling block to trigger. Block is active by default if left blank.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.resetFlagState=The state that the Flag On Reset should be set to.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.fallFlagState=The state that the Flag On Fall should be set to.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.landFlagState=The state that the Flag On Land should be set to.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.maxSpeed=The maximum speed in pixels per second that the block should move.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.acceleration=The acceleration of the block in pixels per second squared.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.direction=The direction the block travels in.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.landingSound=(Optional) File path for a custom landing sound, if desired. Uses standard falling block sounds if left blank.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.returnSound=(Optional) File path for a custom return sound, if desired. Uses standard falling block sounds if left blank.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.shakeSound=(Optional) File path for a custom shake sound, if desired. Uses standard falling block sounds if left blank.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.invertFlagTrigger=If checked, the flag listed by Flag Trigger must be false for this block to be active.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.returnMaxSpeed=The maximum speed in pixels per second that the block should move on its return journey.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/AutoReturnFallingBlock.attributes.description.returnAcceleration=The acceleration of the block in pixels per second squared on its return journey.

