entities.LylyraHelper/DashActivatedDustBunnies/Rotate.attributes.description.DashesPerFullCycle=Number of dashes for the dust bunny to complete a full circle.


#Set Flag States On Respawn Trigger

triggers.LylyraHelper/SS2024/SetFlagStatesOnRespawnTrigger.placements.name.main=Set Flag States On Respawn Trigger
triggers.LylyraHelper/SS2024/SetFlagStatesOnRespawnTrigger.placements.description.main=When touched, this trigger will record the status of a set of specified session flags as they were in that moment.\nWhenenever the player respawns, the session flags are reset to the recorded state.\nExtremely useful for maps that make use of toggled flag triggered mechanics in which the player will regularly navigate the room with both versions of the flag set (for example, a map with a room which can be either underwater or above water).
triggers.LylyraHelper/SS2024/SetFlagStatesOnRespawnTrigger.attributes.description.flags=The set of flags to monitor and record states for when this trigger is entered.

#SMW Key / Whimsy Key

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/WhimsyKey.placements.name.WhimsyKey=Whimsy Key
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/WhimsyKey.placements.description.WhimsyKey=A throwable item that opens Whimsy Doors, as first seen in Forest of Doors by Worldwaker2.\nThe key has mixed motion physics somewhere between a Theo Crystal and a Jellyfish as well as a Jump Thru attached on top.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/WhimsyKey.attributes.description.grabbable=Whether or not this key should be grabbable / throwable.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/WhimsyKey.attributes.description.spritePath=(Optional) Path to a custom sprite animations.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/WhimsyKey.attributes.description.optimized=Reduces computational demands of the key in exchange for slightly less accurate collision checks.\nUseful if you want a room with 50+ keys, or your room is suffering from performance issues.

#Mute Sound Source Trigger

triggers.LylyraHelper/MuteSoundSourceTrigger.placements.name.main=Mute Sound Source Trigger
triggers.LylyraHelper/MuteSoundSourceTrigger.placements.description.main=Mutes audio sources that play via SoundSource.cs, such as Kevin Blocks.\nBasically removes most sounds that VivHelper's Audio Muter does not.\nDoes not work on generic Audio calls, this is specifically for Sound Sources.\nSomething counts a s a soundsource if it emits purple circles while viewing debug hitboxes.
triggers.LylyraHelper/MuteSoundSourceTrigger.attributes.description.unmute=If checked, will unmute previously muted sound(s).
triggers.LylyraHelper/MuteSoundSourceTrigger.attributes.description.sound=The sound(s) to mute or unmute. You may specify multiple sounds using commas.\nExample: event:/game/06_reflection/crushblock_move_loop,event:/game/06_reflection/crushblock_move_loop_covert\n\nSounds that you specify will be added/removed from a persistent session list.
triggers.LylyraHelper/MuteSoundSourceTrigger.attributes.description.muteActiveSourcesOnEnter=If checked, the game will attempt to forcibly mute active sound sources making the sound that you want muted when the trigger is entered.\nHas no effect if unmute is also checked.

#Kuwahara Blur Filter

entities.LylyraHelper/KuwaharaBlurController.placements.name.main=Light Source Sensitive Kuwahara Blur Controller
entities.LylyraHelper/KuwaharaBlurController.placements.description.main=Allows you to disable or enable a Kuwahara Style Blur.\nAreas affected by light sources (including player spotlight) have immunity to this effect proportional to the light's strength.
entities.LylyraHelper/KuwaharaBlurController.attributes.description.flag=The session flag to trigger on.
entities.LylyraHelper/KuwaharaBlurController.attributes.description.on=If checked, will turn Kuwahara bluring on until another Controller turns it off.\nThis persists between rooms and deaths.
entities.LylyraHelper/KuwaharaBlurController.attributes.description.oneTime=If this controller should remove itself after the flag is set.

#Disable Entity Preservation Trigger

triggers.LylyraHelper/DisableEntityPreservationTrigger.placements.name.main=Disable Entity Preservation Trigger
triggers.LylyraHelper/DisableEntityPreservationTrigger.placements.description.main=A trigger that once touched, disables the esoteric tech known as "Entity Preservation", a frame perfect trick that allows a player to die on the frame a temporarily existing entity spawns to bring it into the room upon respawn.\nVery useful if you are making a map with entities that spawn other entities, such as LylyraHelper's Slicers, FrostHelper's GrowBlocks, and many many more.
triggers.LylyraHelper/DisableEntityPreservationTrigger.attributes.description.activate=If checked, disables Entity Preservation upon touching this trigger. If not checked, reenables Entity Preservation instead.


#Cursed Refill


entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/CursedRefill.placements.name.CursedRefill=Cursed Refill
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/CursedRefill.placements.description.CursedRefill=A refill that "curses" the player with death upon the end of their dash, unless an Uncursed Refill is picked up beforehand.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/CursedRefill.attributes.description.textureLocation=A filepath to folder containing the Cursed Refill texture files. See LylyraHelper's Graphics/Atlases/Gameplay/objects/LylyraHelper/ss2024/cursedRefill/ folder for a template of the images needed.

#Uncursed Refill

entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/UncursedRefill.placements.name.UncursedRefill=Uncursed Refill
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/UncursedRefill.placements.description.UncursedRefill=A refill that can only be picked up if the player is under the effects of a curse from a Cursed Refill.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/UncursedRefill.attributes.description.oneUse=If checked, this refill will not respawn until the current room is reloaded / the player respawns.
entities.LylyraHelper/SS2024/UncursedRefill.attributes.description.textureLocation=A filepath to folder containing the Cursed Refill texture files. See LylyraHelper's Graphics/Atlases/Gameplay/objects/LylyraHelper/ss2024/uncursedRefill/ folder for a template of the images needed.
